text: Bennebroek is a former municipality in the Dutch province of North Holland. Since 2009, it has been part of the municipality of Bloemendaal. In 2007, 5,162 people lived there. It was the smallest municipality in the Netherlands, covering an area of only 1.75 kmÂ².
